§ 147. Again, if a goldsmith agrees to make me rings of a certain weight and fashion out of his own gold for, say, two hundred denarii, it is a question whether the con- tract is purcliase and sale or letting and hiring. Cassius says the ma- terial is bought and sold, the labour is let and hired, but most writers hold that there is only a purchase and sale.
